property.htmlValue: A New user story is one that has been added to the product backlog and not yet been reviewed by the product owner nor agreed to build. Such a user story lacks detail the team would need to implement it. Low-priority user stories often remain in the New state, while high-priority stories move quickly to the Approved state.
property.name: documentation
property.value: A New user story is one that has been added to the product backlog and not yet been reviewed by the product owner nor agreed to build. Such a user story lacks detail the team would need to implement it. Low-priority user stories often remain in the New state, while high-priority stories move quickly to the Approved state.

property.htmlValue: An Approved user story is one that the product owner has reviewed and agreed to implement. It is sufficiently detailed and is a candidate to be assigned to a sprint at the sprint planning meeting.
property.name: documentation
property.value: An Approved user story is one that the product owner has reviewed and agreed to implement. It is sufficiently detailed and is a candidate to be assigned to a sprint at the sprint planning meeting.

property.htmlValue: Committed user stories are stories that the team has committed to implement in the next sprint. User stories in the Committed state must be estimated and decomposed into tasks.
property.name: documentation
property.value: Committed user stories are stories that the team has committed to implement in the next sprint. User stories in the Committed state must be estimated and decomposed into tasks.

property.htmlValue: A user story that has been implemented and has fulfilled its acceptance criteria. In sprint review, the product owner inspects the work the team has done and if he/she agrees it meets the acceptance criteria. If the result is positive, the user story is said to be Done.
property.name: documentation
property.value: A user story that has been implemented and has fulfilled its acceptance criteria. In sprint review, the product owner inspects the work the team has done and if he/she agrees it meets the acceptance criteria. If the result is positive, the user story is said to be Done.

property.htmlValue: The user story is no longer needed to be implemented. This happens when the user story is found out of scope, or when product requirements or other work conditions have changed.
property.name: documentation
property.value: The user story is no longer needed to be implemented. This happens when the user story is found out of scope, or when product requirements or other work conditions have changed.

property.htmlValue: A user story is deemed incomplete when the definition of done for the story was incomplete, or when the acceptance criteria for the story is not met. In general, the story is incomplete even if one acceptance criteria is not met.
property.name: documentation
